  "texts": [
    "It can be interpreted as the change in the function value when x undergoes a small perturbation 𝛿: f (x + 𝛿) = f (x) + 𝛿f ′ (x).",
    "Moving x in the opposite direction of the derivative by a small step can decrease f (x).",
    "This technique is known as gradient descent.",
    "When the derivative is 0, we cannot determine the direction in which x should move.",
    "As shown in Figure 3(a), different types of critical points exist in such cases."
